Mycobacterium tuberculosis UM 1072388579 is a clinical isolate of extensively drug-resistant strain, obtained from a patient of University Malaya Medical Centre. It is the first isolated XDR-TB strain in Malaysia. It is resistant to amikacin, capromycin, ciprofloxacin, ethionamide, isoniazid, kanamycin, ofloxacin, rifampicin, and streptomycin but sensitive to ethambutol and para salicylic acid.

Comments: Mycobacterium tuberculosis strain H37RV. This strain has been derived from the original human-lung H37 isolate in 1934, and has been used extensively worldwide in biomedical research. Unlike some clinical isolates, it retains full virulence in animal models of tuberculosis and is susceptible to drugs and receptive to genetic manipulation.
